---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Sewing — Needlework Terms That Score Big"
  description="Sewing and needlework words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. THIMBLE (14pts), BOBBIN (12pts), QUILTED (17pts). Textile vocabulary for competitive players."
  keywords="scrabble sewing words, thimble scrabble points, bobbin scrabble, quilted scrabble word, needlework scrabble, textile words scrabble, craft words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Sewing — Needlework Terms That Score Big","description":"Sewing and needlework words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. THIMBLE (14pts), BOBBIN (12pts), QUILTED (17pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-sewing"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is QUILTED a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! QUILTED scores 17 points (Q=10, U=1, I=1, L=1, T=1, E=1, D=2). It uses the valuable Q tile and is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is THIMBLE in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"THIMBLE scores 14 points (T=1, H=4, I=1, M=3, B=3, L=1, E=1). The H=4, M=3, and B=3 tiles combine for strong mid-range scoring from a 7-letter word."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What sewing words use high-value tiles in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"QUILTED (17pts) uses Q=10, THIMBLE (14pts) combines H+M+B, and BOBBIN (12pts) doubles up on B=3. Sewing vocabulary is excellent for placing B, H, and K tiles effectively."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Sewing — Needlework Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The sewing basket is packed with Scrabble winners. Needlework terminology delivers words heavy in B, H, K, and Q tiles — letters that often feel stuck on your rack. From QUILTED to THIMBLE, these craft words consistently deliver 12-17 point plays from common letter combinations.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QUILTED (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">THIMBLE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BOBBIN</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">STITCH</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Q-Powered Quilting Word</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">QUILTED — 17 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">Q=10, U=1, I=1, L=1, T=1, E=1, D=2 · 7 letters · Uses Q tile</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Stitched through layers of fabric with padding. QUILTED gets most of its power from Q=10, making it one of the easiest Q words to remember. As a 7-letter word, it can potentially earn the 50-point bingo bonus if you use all your tiles.</p>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Essential Sewing Tools</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧵 THIMBLE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · T=1, H=4, I=1, M=3, B=3, L=1, E=1 · Finger protector</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🪡 BOBBIN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · B=3, O=1, B=3, B=3, I=1, N=1 · Thread spool</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✂️ SHEARS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · S=1, H=4, E=1, A=1, R=1, S=1 · Cutting tool</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📌 NEEDLE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 pts · N=1, E=1, E=1, D=2, L=1, E=1 · Basic tool</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Sewing Techniques & Actions</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">STITCH</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HEMMED</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DARNED</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BASTED</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PLEAT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TACKED</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Sewing Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QUILTED for bingo potential:</span> At exactly 7 letters, QUILTED can earn the 50-point bingo bonus (67 total). Keep Q+U+I+L on your rack and fish for T, E, D.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BOBBIN uses double B:</span> If you're stuck with two B tiles (B=3 each), BOBBIN clears both for 12 points. The double-letter tiles that feel like dead weight become an asset.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">HEMMED and TACKED for K/H racks:</span> Both words place H=4 or K=5 effectively. HEMMED (13pts) doubles the M tile, while TACKED (13pts) uses K=5 with common letters.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Sewing words excel at <span class="text-white font-medium">placing double consonants</span> — BOBBIN (double B), HEMMED (double M), NEEDLE (double E). When your rack has duplicates that feel stuck, think needlework. These words turn duplicate-heavy racks into 10+ point plays.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-textiles/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Textiles</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-clothing-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Clothing Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-q-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Q Words in Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid sewing word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
